\title{yieldcurves: Yield Curve Fitting, Analysis, and Decomposition}
\description{
Fits yield curves using Nelson-Siegel (1987) \doi{10.1086/296409}, Svensson (1994) \doi{10.3386/w4871}, and cubic spline methods. Extracts forward rates, discount factors, and par rates from fitted curves. Computes duration and convexity risk measures. Provides principal component decomposition following Litterman and Scheinkman (1991) \doi{10.3905/jfi.1991.692347}, carry and roll-down analysis, and slope measures. All methods are pure computation with no external dependencies beyond base R; works with yield data from any source.
